dialogue: Hi De-an! My name is Frosty :penguin: and Im here to help you learn all about science:microscope:, verbal reasoning (GRE) :input_latin_uppercase:, and safety:hammer_and_wrench:!
Okay! Lets see how much you know about safety!
Which fire extinguishers are used to put out fires caused by flammable liquids?
Safety first! Here's some questions on safety!
Alrighty, which of the following options is the answer of the question?

:keycap_1: Class C dry chemical fire extinguisher
:keycap_2: Class B carbon dioxide fire extinguisher
:keycap_3: Class A water fire extinguishers
See if you can answer this next one.
Which fire extinguishers are used to put out Class A fires?
It's one of the following choices.

:keycap_1: Both water and multi-purpose dry chemical
:keycap_2: Multi-purpose dry chemical only
:keycap_3: Water only
:keycap_4: CO2 only
:keycap_5: Both CO2 and water
The correct answer is Both water and multi-purpose dry chemical.
Okay, which subject would you like to choose?:backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-light_skin_tone:
Awesome! Let's learn about the GRE!
Could you answer this one for me?
Possessing few natural resources upon its newly-granted independence in 1863, Singapore remained economically _____ until an influx of industrialization and foreign investment took hold there.
Pick one of the following answers.
That wasn't quite what we were looking for. :disappointed_face:
I hope this explanation could help you understand the the question.
:pushpin: Dubious -- fraught with uncertainty or doubt
Having squandered his life's savings on unprofitable business ventures, the _____ entrepreneur was forced to live in squalor.
Okay. Which of these is the right answer?:backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-light_skin_tone:
Yes! You got the correct answer!
I hope this explanation could help you understand the the question.

:pushpin: Insolvent -- unable to meet or discharge financial obligations
:pushpin: Former -- preceding in time; prior or earlier
:pushpin: Unlikely -- not likely to be true or to occur or to have occurred
:pushpin: Perturbed -- thrown into a state of agitated confusion
:pushpin: Eccentric -- conspicuously or grossly unconventional or unusual
Please type your answer in if you know it :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
Dolly Madison, the wife of President James Madison, was known especially for her _____ , remaining calm even as the British invaded Washington D.C. during the War of 1812.
Alrighty, which of the following options is the answer of the question?

:pushpin: Equanimity -- steadiness of mind under stress
:pushpin: Impracticality -- concerned with theoretical possibilities rather than actual use
:pushpin: Cynicism -- a cynical feeling of distrust
:pushpin: Zeal -- a feeling of strong eagerness usually in favor of a person or cause
:pushpin: Malevolence -- wishing evil to others
Even though legislators claimed the Contagious Diseases Acts strengthened the nation, social purists argued the Acts _____ the nation's moral growth by encouraging licentious behavior.
It's one of the following choices.
Let's take a look at this question.
Many Major League Baseball relief pitchers choose an electrifying theme song to play as they take the mound; the song _____ their fans and instills fear in their opponents.
Okay. I'll give you some choices.
I'm sorry, but that was incorrect. :disappointed_face:

:pushpin: Innervates -- to supply with nerves
:pushpin: Eviscerates -- surgically remove a part of a structure or an organ
:pushpin: Enervates -- weaken mentally or morally
:pushpin: Assuages -- cause to be more favorably inclined; gain the good will of
:pushpin: Pervades -- spread or diffuse through
Cool, let's pick one of the following subjects?:backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-light_skin_tone:
Awesome! Here are some questions on science!
Let's see if you can get this one.
The lithosphere is divided into a dozen major and several minor what?
Alrighty, which of the following options is the answer of the question?
This is an explanation of the question:

The lithosphere is divided into a dozen major and several minor plates. Each plate is named for the continent or ocean basin it contains. Some plates are made of all oceanic lithosphere. A few are all continental lithosphere. But most plates are made of a combination of both.
